name: Categorizes Temporal Primes
description: Classifies temporal prime elements into fundamental categories that span the space of possible dynamical behaviors.
subject: urn:uor:resource:temporal-prime-decomposition
contextualDescription: The Temporal Prime Decomposition resource categorizes temporal prime elements into five fundamental types (oscillatory, growth/decay, transition, fluctuation, and attractor primes) that together span the space of possible dynamical behaviors observed in natural and artificial systems.
